{
  "stem": "21786.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 15.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The border became open until the end of March.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If somebody had, for instance, a passport, he could leave for 14 days.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "At that point, simply, they stopped all the traffic.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "For the Jews, they simply seized-- within 24 hours-- they seized all the Jewish accounts, anything what has got-- what had to do something with money, or with any kind of valuables.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They blocked all the safes, all the deposit boxes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And within literally two months, they released all the public employees who were Jews-- all the professors or teachers at schools, at universities, at public offices.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They-- literally, every day-- every day, I may be exaggerating-- but every week, there was a different kind of ordinance or different kind of bylaw, different kinds of order issued to the Jewish community, which then had the duty to spread it among its members, or people who were considered for Jewish, limiting, I mean, anything one can imagine.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "In other words, we were not permitted to use the trains.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We are not permitted to leave Prague.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We are not permitted to move in certain parts of the city.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Eventually, we were given the curfew of 8 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We were not permitted to buy things in any store, with exception of stores which were designed-- designated for Jews.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And only a certain food was given to Jews, and in certain quantity on certain days.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The Jews couldn't buy anything connected to art, to music.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My life changed simply that I felt that I made a catastrophic mistake that I didn't leave.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I couldn't imagine what will happen.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I somehow had the feeling that something extremely odd is happening, and very sinister is happening.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
